Variant Channeling - Ale/Wine			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.28	DESC:Heal - Creatures ignore the nauseated and sickened conditions, as well as ability damage and drain from poison, until the end of your next turn. This does not bring back to life creatures killed by Constitution damage.  Harm - Creatures are nauseated for 1 round.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Art/Music		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.28	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain a +%1 channel bonus on Perform checks and on saving throws against illusions, sonic effects, and language-dependent effects for 1 minute.  Harm - Creatures take a -%1 channel penalty on saving throws against illusions, sonic effects, and language-dependent effects for 1 minute.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Battle/Wrath		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.28	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain a +%1 channel bonus on weapon damage and critical hit confirmation rolls until the end of your next turn. Harm - Creatures take a -%1 channel penalty on weapon damage and critical hit confirmation rolls until the end of your next turn.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Beauty/Love/Lust	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain a +%1 channel bonus on saving throws against charm effects and abilities based on fascination or physical attractiveness (such as a nymph's blinding beauty and stunning glance abilities) for 1 minute. Harm - Creatures gain a -%1 channel penalty on saving throws against charm effects and effects that fascinate for 1 minute.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Bravery/Valor		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures affected by fear may attempt another saving throw and receive a +%1 channel bonus on the roll. A creature unaffected by fear gains a +%1 channel bonus to its Armor Class until the end of your next turn and on its attack roll if it makes a charge attack before your next turn. Harm - This works like a standard channel (not halved).	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Cities			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain a +%1 channel bonus on attack rolls when flanking and to Armor Class when flanked until the end of your next turn. Harm - All creatures' squares and threatened areas are treated as difficult terrain until the start of your next turn (these areas move with the creatures rather than being fixed in place at the time of the channeling). Until the end of your next turn, creatures gain a -%1 channel penalty on Acrobatics checks and overrun attempts to move through these squares.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Contracts/Oaths	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain a +%1 channel bonus on saves against compulsion effects until the end of your next turn. Harm - Creatures gain a -%1 channel penalty on saving throws against compulsions until the end of your next turn.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Darkness			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain low-light vision until the end of your next turn. At cleric level 5, they gain darkvision 30 feet as well, increasing this range by 30 feet for every 5 cleric levels thereafter. Harm - The illumination level in the area drops by 1 step, as darkness, for 1 minute. At cleric level 10, the light level drops by 2 steps. At cleric level 15, it drops by 3 steps, and areas of dim light or darkness become supernaturally dark (even creatures with darkvision cannot see within it).	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Death			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain a +%1 channel bonus on stabilization checks when dying and on saves against death effects for 1 minute. Harm - Creatures gain a -%1 channel penalty on stabilization checks when dying for 1 minute, and subtract the channel penalty from all healing magic, fast healing, and regeneration.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Destruction		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain a +%1 channel bonus on attack and damage rolls against objects, CMB for sunder attempts, and Strength checks to break objects until the end of your next turn. Harm - Unattended objects take full channel damage (not half).	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Disease			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures heal %1 points of ability damage to one ability score (your choice). Harm - Creatures are sickened until the end of your next turn, plus %1 rounds. At cleric level 10, you may select one creature as the target of a contagion in addition to the effects of the channeled energy. At cleric level 20, all creatures in the area are subject to contagion in addition to the effects of the channeled energy.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Dreams			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures affected by sleep effects may attempt another saving throw and apply the +%1 channel bonus on the roll. Willingly sleeping creatures gain a +%1 channel bonus on saving throws and Perception checks for up to 8 hours (this bonus ends if the creature awakens). Harm - Creatures gain a -%1 channel penalty on Perception checks and saving throws against exhaustion, fatigue, and sleep effects for 1 minute.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Earth			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain a DR 1/adamantine until the end of your next turn. This DR improves by 1 at 5th level and every 5 levels thereafter. This does not allow recipients to overcome DR/adamantine with their own attacks. Harm - All squares in the area are treated as diff icult terrain for 1 minute.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Envy			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain a +%1 channel bonus on disarm and steal combat maneuvers, Bluff checks, and Sleight of Hand checks for 1 minute. Harm - Creatures must attempt a steal combat maneuver on their next turn against an adjacent enemy. This is a compulsion effect. 	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Farming			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures ignore fatigue (but not exhaustion) for 1 minute. The healing effect is enhanced (see page 28) for plant creatures. Harm - The damage effect is enhanced for plant creatures. Creatures are fatigued, as if experiencing starvation (see page 444 of the Core Rulebook).	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Fate			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain a +%1 channel bonus on one d20 roll made during their next readied action as long as it is taken before the end of your next turn. Harm - Creatures gain a -%1 channel penalty on ability checks and skill checks for 1 minute.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Fire			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - The healing effect is enhanced (see page 28) for creatures with the fire subtype. Harm - The damage effect is enhanced for creatures with the cold subtype. Affected creatures who fail their saves catch on fire (see page 444 of the Core Rulebook).	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Forge			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures in metal armor gain a +%1 channel bonus to Armor Class until the end of your next turn. Alternatively, you may repair damage to metal objects and metal constructs as if they were creatures, and this healing is enhanced (see page 28). Harm - The damage effect is enhanced (see page 28) against metal constructs and unattended metal objects.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
Variant Channeling - Freedom			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.VariantChanneling	SOURCEPAGE:p.29	DESC:Heal - Creatures gain a +%1 channel bonus on Escape Artist checks, CMB checks to escape a grapple, and saving throws against becoming entangled, paralyzed, or slowed. Harm - Creatures are slowed (as slow) until the end of your next turn.	DEFINE:ChannelModifier|0	BONUS:VAR|ChannelModifier|min(5,1+floor(ClericChannelEnergyLVL/5))
