Scourge of the Enemy	KEY:Scourge of the Enemy ~ Zeal Domain	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	DESC:Select one religion that is a rival or opponent of your religion. You treat members of this religion as if they were your favored enemy (as the ranger class ability), gaining a +%1 bonus on the appropriate rolls. These bonuses do not stack with other favored enemy bonuses (use the highest bonus that applies).|ScourgeOfTheEnemyBonus	DEFINE:ScourgeOfTheEnemyBonus|2	BONUS:VAR|ScourgeOfTheEnemyBonus|2|PREVARGTEQ:DomainZealLVL,13	BONUS:VAR|ScourgeOfTheEnemyBonus|2|PREVARGTEQ:DomainZealLVL,18	SOURCEPAGE:p.44

###Block: Monk Vows
# COMMENT: Part of the book says "This section introduces monk vows, which any
# COMMENT:   user of ki can take to increase his ki pool."  So, presumably,
# COMMENT:   ninjas from Ulitmate Combat can use monk vows.  
# COMMENT:   This is not implemented, due to figuring out the appropriate level
# COMMENT:   for non-monk or part-monk/part-other-ki class combinations.
# COMMENT: Take the Vow Monk archetype to activate vows.
1. Vows			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MonkVow	VISIBLE:DISPLAY	COST:1
Vow of Celibacy		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.MonkVow	DESC:You must abstain from all sexual and intimate physical activity. You take it to an extreme, refusing to even share a room with another person, or sleeping on the opposite side of a camp from other people in a group. You are not allowed to touch others or have others touch you (including touch spells from allies). Striking enemies in battle or being struck by enemies is not prohibited, but you shun all peaceful or pleasurable contact.	SOURCEPAGE:p.50	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Monk Archetype ~ Vow Monk	COST:0	BONUS:VAR|KiPoints|max(1,floor(classlevel("Monk")/5))
Vow of Chains		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.MonkVow	DESC:Either out of penitence or to bring attention to the suffering of the enslaved, you wear shackles on your wrists and legs. This gives you a -1 penalty on attack rolls and to AC, and reduces your movement by 10 feet. If temporarily unable to wear your chains, you may carry rocks or some other heavy burden (including medium or heavy armor) to simulate this suffering.	SOURCEPAGE:p.50	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Monk Archetype ~ Vow Monk	COST:0	BONUS:VAR|KiPoints|max(1,floor(classlevel("Monk")/3))	BONUS:COMBAT|AC|-1	BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT|-1	BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Walk|-10
Vow of Cleanliness	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.MonkVow	DESC:You must wash daily. You must change into fresh clothes daily or shortly after your robes become dirty. Your appearance must be kept immaculate, including either neatly braiding or shaving off your hair (and, for male monks, maintaining a clean-shaven face). Your vow forbids you from willingly touching the filthy, diseased, dead, or undead (though you may attempt to cleanse or heal those suffering from disease), though using manufactured weapons to attack these creatures is allowed.	SOURCEPAGE:p.50	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Monk Archetype ~ Vow Monk	COST:0	BONUS:VAR|KiPoints|max(1,floor(classlevel("Monk")/5))
Vow of Fasting		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.MonkVow	DESC:You eat nothing but rice (or a similar bland, staple food) and drink nothing but water. On certain days (usually once per month or on a religious holiday), you may eat a small portion of other simple, bland food to maintain proper nutrition. You cannot use tobacco, drugs, potions, alchemical items requiring eating or drinking, or any other thing that could be considered a food or beverage.	SOURCEPAGE:p.50	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Monk Archetype ~ Vow Monk	COST:0	BONUS:VAR|KiPoints|max(1,floor(classlevel("Monk")/6))
Vow of Peace		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.MonkVow	DESC:You must strive to attain peace and may only use violence as a last resort. You can never strike the first blow in combat. If attacked, you must use the fight defensively action or the total defense action for the first 2 rounds. You must always give your opponent the option to surrender, and cannot purposely slay another creature that could reasonably be influenced to flee or join a civilized society as a productive member (obviously this excludes many monsters). Many monks who have taken this vow learn how to grapple and pin opponents, tying them with specialized knots that allow them to work themselves free after sufficient effort. Many monks of peace are vegetarians.	SOURCEPAGE:p.50	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Monk Archetype ~ Vow Monk	COST:0	BONUS:VAR|KiPoints|max(1,floor(classlevel("Monk")/5))
Vow of Poverty		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.MonkVow	DESC:You must never own more than six possessions - a simple set of clothing, a pair of sandals or shoes, a bowl, a sack, a blanket, and any one other item. Five of these items must be of plain and simple make, though one can be of some value (often an heirloom of great personal significance to you). You can never keep more money or wealth on your person than you need to feed, bathe, and shelter yourself for 1 week in modest accommodations. You cannot borrow or carry wealth or items worth more than 50 gp that belong to others. You are allowed to accept and use curative potions (or similar magical items where the item is consumed and is valueless thereafter) from other creatures.	SOURCEPAGE:p.50	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Monk Archetype ~ Vow Monk	COST:0	BONUS:VAR|KiPoints|max(1,floor(classlevel("Monk")/2))
Vow of Silence		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.MonkVow	DESC:You must speak no words and attempt to be quiet in your actions. Accidental noises and the sounds of battle (such as the sound of a fist or weapon striking an opponent) do not affect your vow, though most monks with this vow choose their weapons and opponents so as to minimize even these sounds. You are allowed to make a nonvocal noise to warn another of danger (such as by stomping or clapping). You are allowed to use gestures and motions to communicate with others (including sign language) and are allowed to write.	SOURCEPAGE:p.51	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Monk Archetype ~ Vow Monk	COST:0	BONUS:VAR|KiPoints|max(1,floor(classlevel("Monk")/6))
Vow of Truth		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.MonkVow	DESC:You are not allowed to deliberately speak any lies, including bluffing, stating half-truths with the intent to deceive, exaggerating, telling white lies, and so on. This applies to all forms of communication. If presented with circumstances where telling the truth would bring harm to another, you remain silent. Many monks of this vow also take a vow of silence to show their commitment.	SOURCEPAGE:p.51	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Monk Archetype ~ Vow Monk	COST:0	BONUS:VAR|KiPoints|max(1,floor(classlevel("Monk")/5))

